grid container padded-container" role="main"> <div tabindex="-1" id="skip-to-content"></div> <header id="top" class="top full-columns" role="presentation"> <div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-dfp" data-pb-name="DFP Ad" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="fL1CDi1dr2QPMr"> </div> <div class="pb-container"> <div class="wrapper clearfix col col-desktop-6 col-tablet-6 col-mobile-6 pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-article-header" data-pb-name="Article Header" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f0zGeE9dr2QPMr"> <div class="crd card "> <div class="crd--cnt card-content align-center "> <ul class="tag-list-wrapper list-unstyled flex-container-row justify-center " role="presentation"> <li> <a class="tag tag-solid tag-first" href="https://www.chicagotribune.com/investigations/#nt=taxonomy-article"> Investigations </a> </li> </ul> <h1 class="spaced spaced-xl spaced-top spaced-bottom abdp-headline">Hurt instead of helped: Foster children victimized in out-of-state facilities where oversight is lacking</h1> </div> <div class="crd--ft card-footer flex-container-row article-header align-items-center justify-space-between "> <div class="byline-container flex-container-row align-items-center"> <div class="byline-image-container hddn-mble spaced spaced-right spaced-sm spaced spaced-right spaced-sm"> <div class="byline-image"> <div class="logo logo-stacked logo-src-1 logo-sm lf-el"></div> </div> </div> <div class="byline-timestamp-container"> <div class="byline-wrapper"> <span class="byline byline-article">By <a class="uppercase" aria-label="David Jackson" href="/chi-david-jackson-staff.html#nt=byline" rel="author"><span class="uppercase">David Jackson</span></a>&nbsp;and <span class="uppercase">Duaa Eldeib</span> </span> </div> <span class="spaced spaced-right spaced-md hddn-mble"></span> <div class="timestamp-wrapper flex-container-row align-items-center flex-mobile-column "> <div class="align-center"> <span class="timestamp timestamp-article">Chicago Tribune</span> <span class="timestamp spaced spaced-sm spaced-left spaced-right hddn-mble" aria-hidden="true">|</span> </div> <div> <span class="timestamp timestamp-article "> Mar 12, 2020 </span> <span class="timestamp spaced spaced-sm spaced-left spaced-right hddn-tbl" aria-hidden="true">|</span> <span class="timestamp timestamp-article hddn-tbl "> 6:00 AM </span> </div> </div> </div> </div> <span class="sharebar "> <button class="svg-c button button-icon button-icon-hover-accent " aria-label="share on twitter" name="twitter" onclick="window.open( 'https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Hurt+instead+of+helped%3A+Foster+children+victimized+in+out-of-state+facilities+where+oversight+is+lacking&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagotribune.com%2Finvestigations%2Fct-foster-children-sent-out-of-state-illinois-dcfs-20200311-lqmwptbnrrc3nkygenhelm6nri-htmlstory.html', 'share_popup', 'height=500,width=650' ); return false;" role="button" data-arctrack="socialShareTwtr" data-referrer="story" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <svg class="icon-margin-auto button-icon-inset-accent icon-16-17" focusable="false"> <use xlink:href="#twitter"/> </svg> </button> <button class="svg-c button button-icon button-icon-hover-accent " name="facebook" aria-label="share on facebook" onclick="window.open( 'https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagotribune.com%2Finvestigations%2Fct-foster-children-sent-out-of-state-illinois-dcfs-20200311-lqmwptbnrrc3nkygenhelm6nri-htmlstory.html&title=Hurt+instead+of+helped%3A+Foster+children+victimized+in+out-of-state+facilities+where+oversight+is+lacking', 'share_popup', 'height=500,width=650' ); return false;" data-arctrack="socialShareFb" data-referrer="story" data-href="https://www.chicagotribune.com/investigations/ct-foster-children-sent-out-of-state-illinois-dcfs-20200311-lqmwptbnrrc3nkygenhelm6nri-htmlstory.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <svg class="icon-margin-auto button-icon-inset-accent icon-16-17" focusable="false"> <use xlink:href="#facebook-square"/> </svg> </button> <a class="svg-c button button-icon button-icon-hover-accent " href="mailto:?subject=Hurt%20instead%20of%20helped%3A%20Foster%20children%20victimized%20in%20out-of-state%20facilities%20where%20oversight%20is%20lacking&body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagotribune.com%2Finvestigations%2Fct-foster-children-sent-out-of-state-illinois-dcfs-20200311-lqmwptbnrrc3nkygenhelm6nri-htmlstory.html" role="button" aria-label="share story via email" data-arctrack="socialShareEmail" data-referrer="story" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <svg class="icon-margin-auto button-icon-inset-accent icon-16-17" focusable="false"> <use xlink:href="#share"/> </svg> </a> </span> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-utilities-lead-art" data-pb-name="Lead Art" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="fFGgDv1dr2QPMr"> <div class="crd card-captioned "> <div class="crd--cnt artcl--fll--ldt"> <figure class="" data-trk-photo-credit="Stacey Wescott/Chicago Tribune"> <div class="full-width img-container aspect-ratio-no-aspect"> <img class="no-lazy full-width" alt="An employee of Millcreek Behavioral Health walks last fall with two young residents on the facility&#039;s campus in Fordyce, Arkansas. Millcreek has emerged as a national hub for treating children with emotional and behavioral disorders." src="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/sVGnZCRT4AnHQe_rBPf4X8bStF8=/415x274/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/5VCBQZCVCJG65NQXNQZGK42XAE.JPG" data-src="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/dbCQR3DhTzxOTVVf-_YasvGIug4=/1200x794/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/5VCBQZCVCJG65NQXNQZGK42XAE.JPG" data-src-small="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/sVGnZCRT4AnHQe_rBPf4X8bStF8=/415x274/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/5VCBQZCVCJG65NQXNQZGK42XAE.JPG" data-src-medium="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/0_Bg_iqY1kmsIkbuKXqWlR-yKJI=/800x529/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/5VCBQZCVCJG65NQXNQZGK42XAE.JPG" data-src-mobile="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/sVGnZCRT4AnHQe_rBPf4X8bStF8=/415x274/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/5VCBQZCVCJG65NQXNQZGK42XAE.JPG"/> </div> <figcaption class="caption-text spaced spaced-top spaced-sm flex-container-row justify-space-between "> <div>An employee of Millcreek Behavioral Health walks last fall with two young residents on the facility's campus in Fordyce, Arkansas. Millcreek has emerged as a national hub for treating children with emotional and behavioral disorders.(Stacey Wescott/Chicago Tribune)</div> </figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> </div> <div id="f0TtJf2dr2QPMr" class="pb-async pb-feature"></div> <div class="pb-container"> </div> </header> <article id="main" role="main" class="four-column guttered full-columns"> <div class="wrapper clearfix col full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-article-body" data-pb-name="Article Body (Elements)" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f0PkRPCdr2QPMr"> <div class=""> </div> <div class="artcl--fll--pg clln clln-crd overflow-auto cs__ctn__border-bottom"> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p data-page="1" data-item-type="depthscroll" data-item-id="depth_scroll_top" data-item-number="top"> <i>This story is a collaboration between the Chicago Tribune and ProPublica Illinois.</i></p> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> Across the country, child welfare officials have sent thousands of foster children to mental health institutions in distant states, including facilities where children reported being beaten and sexually assaulted by other residents or mistreated by workers.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> The journeys of these children resemble an airline flight map: California to Virginia, Florida to Utah, Hawaii to Arkansas. Illinois officials have transported children as young as 7 to facilities in more than a dozen states.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> One Chicago girl who was placed at institutions in Arkansas, Michigan, Ohio and Tennessee said she was sedated, subjected to bruising restraints and sexually assaulted by a facility employee, according to government records and interviews.</p> </div></div> <div class="mobile-dfp inline-ad hddn-mble hddn-tbl" data-inline-ad-count="2"> <span class="hddn-mble"><div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo" data-pb-name="Nativo Ad" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f4d7Zf1A7ogLWr"> <div id="19568" class="trb_ar_nt"> </div> </div></span> <span class="hddn-mble hidden-tablet"><div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo" data-pb-name="Nativo Ad" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f4d7Zf1A7ogLWr"> <div id="19568" class="trb_ar_nt"> </div> </div></span> </div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> “I basically felt like I was abandoned, like nobody wants to deal with me,” said the girl, who is now 17.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="interstitial_link" class="crd clln--it" data-interstitial="auto"> <div class="crd--cnt"> <span class="roadblock"> <strong><a href="https://www.chicagotribune.com/coronavirus/ct-coronavirus-pandemic-chicago-illinois-news-20200420-fiyolw53xfhtvjdijyswhcwxei-story.html#nt=interstitial-auto">[Most read] Coronavirus in Illinois updates: Officials report 1,151 new known COVID-19 cases and 59 additional deaths statewide, as Pritzker says hospitalizations up 7% from 5 days ago <span aria-hidden="true">»</span></a></strong> </span> </div></div><div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> Illinois officials also sent a 16-year-old boy to a facility in Indiana where police have been called to investigate dozens of battery allegations, including attacks that left children with broken bones or in need of hospital care.</p> </div></div> <div class="inline-ad hidden-desktop"> <div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo" data-pb-name="Nativo Ad" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f0tkbBNR7ogLWr"> <div id="6394" class="trb_ar_nt_m" data-ad-lite="true"> </div> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> “When I first got there, I got jumped every day by kids and staff,” said the boy, now 18.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="image" class="crd card-captioned clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <figure class="" data-trk-photo-credit="Taylor Glascock/for ProPublica Illinois"> <div class="full-width img-container aspect-ratio-no-aspect"> <img class="b-lazy full-width" alt="An 18-year-old boy, shown walking in a Chicago suburb last August, spent nearly a year at Campagna Academy in Indiana after becoming a ward of the state at age 16. &quot;When I first got there, I got jumped every day by kids and staff,&quot; he said." data-src="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/D2_rFjpi7OzlzWWb9MIvwyPjA_Y=/1400x0/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/PK2RMI5T7RE6NB6DMQYXV525GM.JPG" data-src-small="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/NoWe5RCt0giId3xP3IGiumoPO7I=/415x276/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/PK2RMI5T7RE6NB6DMQYXV525GM.JPG" data-src-medium="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/AYAgR1jUYeX6aJLXQ8gRkhriXm0=/800x533/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/PK2RMI5T7RE6NB6DMQYXV525GM.JPG" data-src-mobile="https://www.chicagotribune.com/resizer/NoWe5RCt0giId3xP3IGiumoPO7I=/415x276/top/arc-anglerfish-arc2-prod-tronc.s3.amazonaws.com/public/PK2RMI5T7RE6NB6DMQYXV525GM.JPG" src="/pb/resources/images/tinygif.gif"> </div> <figcaption class="caption-text spaced spaced-top spaced-sm flex-container-row justify-space-between "> <div>An 18-year-old boy, shown walking in a Chicago suburb last August, spent nearly a year at Campagna Academy in Indiana after becoming a ward of the state at age 16. "When I first got there, I got jumped every day by kids and staff," he said. (Taylor Glascock/for ProPublica Illinois)</div> </figcaption> </figure> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> Oregon officials placed a 9-year-old girl in an institution in Montana and didn’t visit her again for nearly six months, when they found her unwashed in an oversized hospital shirt, interviews and records show.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> “It’s not right they send us so far from home,” the girl, now 10, said in a telephone interview. </p> </div></div> <div data-type="text" class="crd clln--it"> <div class=" crd--cnt "> <p> Officials in Illinois and other states acknowledge they sent wards out of state to private facilities despite having a limited capacity to monitor the children’s care and safety. A Chicago Tribune-ProPublica Illinois investigation found repeated breakdowns in oversight as states — those sending the children as well as those receiving them — failed to protect young people in need of specialized care.</p> </div></div> <div data-type="interstitial_link" class="crd clln--it" data-interstitial="auto"> <div class="crd--cnt"> <span class="roadblock"> <strong><a href="https://www.chicagotribune.com/coronavirus/ct-life-quarantine-self-pleasure-sexual-wellness-0420-20200421-butw7la5hfbe5lmlt6b7mv4sye-story.html#nt=interstitial-auto">[Most read] ‘Masturbation will not spread COVID-19’: Solo sex is best option for pleasure during quarantine, especially if you live alone <span aria-hidden="true">»</span></a></strong> </span> </div></div><div class="inline-ad hidden-desktop"> <div class="wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-dfp" data-pb-name="DFP Ad" data-pb-curated="curated" data-pb-id="unnamed-feature" id="f0ARhduf8ogLWr"> <div class="pb-ad pb-ad-prod ad-300x250 hddn-dktp relativehddn-dktp"> <div class="ad-caption-text align-center uppercase">Advertisement</div> <div id="news_1734" class="hddn" data-optimera-measure="trb_ad_300x250_adLiteCube_2_/investigations/ct-foster-children-sent-out-of-state-illinois-dcfs-20200"> </div> </div> <script>
